8 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require the
9 Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation (Commissioner) to develop a
10 plan for reducing the number of delayed timber harvests on State Forest lands.
11 The bill would require the report to include a summary of the status of timber
12 harvests on State Forest lands, including the number of harvests that have not
13 been completed by the initial scheduled date of harvest and the reasons for any
14 delayed harvests. The bill would require the Commissioner to propose how to
15 reduce the number of delayed timber harvests on State Forest lands, including
16 whether additional staff at the Department of Forests, Parks and Recreation are
17 needed to conduct the work necessary for completion of timber harvests. In
18 addition, the Commissioner shall address in the report whether licensed private
19 foresters could be contracted with to conduct the work necessary to reduce the
20 number of delayed timber harvests. The bill would require the Commissioner
21 in the report to estimate the costs and benefits of any plan to reduce the number
